<h1 id="manage-versions">Manage versions</h1>

<p>Versions will be used, e.g. for roadmap planning to track certain product versions or releases. Work packages can be assigned to a version. They will be displayed in the <a href="../../../roadmap">Roadmap</a>.</p>

<p>Also, version will  be used to enable the Backlogs module, i.e. to create a product backlog and sprints in OpenProject.</p>

<p><a href="../../../backlogs-scrum/manage-sprints">Read here how to create a new backlogs version</a>.</p>

<h2 id="create-a-new-version">Create a new version</h2>

<p>Press the green <strong>+ Version</strong> button to create a new version for a project.</p>

<p><img src="User-guide-project-settins-versions.png" alt="User-guide-project-settins-versions" /></p>

<p>You can configure the following information.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Set a <strong>name</strong> for the version.</li>
  <li>Add a <strong>description</strong> to specify the version.</li>
  <li>Set <strong>status</strong> of a version, the default status is open.</li>
  <li>Choose a <strong>wiki page</strong> that you want to open directly from a version in the Roadmap.</li>
  <li>Set a <strong>start date and finish date</strong> for the version.</li>
  <li>Choose whether the version shall be <strong>shared</strong> with other projects, e.g. in the project hierarchy or subprojects.</li>
  <li>Select a <strong>column in backlogs view</strong>. This is only required if you use the versions to manage your <a href="../../../backlogs-scrum">Scrum backlog</a>.</li>
  <li>Press the blue <strong>Create</strong> button to save your changes.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="User-guide-project-settings-create-version.png" alt="User-guide-project-settings-create-version" /></p>

<h2 id="edit-or-delete-versions">Edit or delete versions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Click on the name of a version to <strong>edit</strong> it or on the edit icon at the right in the row.</li>
  <li>Press the <strong>delete</strong> button at the right of the version to delete a version.</li>
  <li>You can <strong>close all completed versions</strong> with the button at the bottom of the list. In order to close only certain versions, open the details view and adapt the version <strong>Status</strong> (see above).</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="User-guide-project-settings-edit-versions.png" alt="User-guide-project-settings-edit-versions" /></p>

<h2 id="close-a-version">Close a version</h2>

<p>To close a version, open the details view of a version and set the <strong>Status</strong> to <em>Closed</em>.</p>

<p><img src="image-20200129161010953.png" alt="close version" /></p>
